<p dir="auto">Rynn UI is a simple and easy-to-use API documentation interface built with Express.js. It allows developers to quickly set up and view API documentation with customizable settings using a <code>settings.json</code> file.</p>
<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h2 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Features</h2><a id="user-content-features" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: Features" href="https://github.com/alzzhosting/kenz-api/blob/main/README.md#features"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>Simple API documentation interface</li>
<li>Easily customizable with a <code>settings.json</code> file</li>
<li>Categorized APIs for easy navigation</li>
<li>Includes real-time settings such as name, version, description, and creator</li>
<li>Supports image display in the UI for branding</li>
<li>Links to external resources such as source code and contact info</li>
</ul>

<p dir="auto"><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://camo.githubusercontent.com/afd57a6fbdac2c9d5f30d60b4f753ba592a1f1d4019f728bbdb87a9a3f4e5b24/68747470733a2f2f66696c65732e636174626f782e6d6f652f626a617a71622e706e67"><img src="https://camo.githubusercontent.com/afd57a6fbdac2c9d5f30d60b4f753ba592a1f1d4019f728bbdb87a9a3f4e5b24/68747470733a2f2f66696c65732e636174626f782e6d6f652f626a617a71622e706e67" alt="Layout" data-canonical-src="https://files.catbox.moe/bjazqb.png" style="max-width: 100%;"></a></p>
<p dir="auto">You can easily customize the UI by editing the <code>settings.json</code> file. Below is a breakdown of the configurable fields:</p>
<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h3 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">General Settings</h3><a id="user-content-general-settings" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: General Settings" href="https://github.com/alzzhosting/kenz-api/blob/main/README.md#general-settings"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><code>name</code>: Sets the name of your API (e.g., "Rynn Api's").</li>
<li><code>version</code>: Specifies the version of your API interface (e.g., "Rynn UI").</li>
<li><code>description</code>: A brief description of your API documentation.</li>
</ul>
<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h3 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Header Customization</h3><a id="user-content-header-customization" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: Header Customization" href="https://github.com/alzzhosting/kenz-api/blob/main/README.md#header-customization"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><code>status</code>: Indicates the current status of your API (e.g., "Online!").</li>
<li><code>imageSrc</code>: An array of image URLs to display in the header. Multiple images can be set for variety.</li>
<li><code>imageSize</code>: Defines responsive image sizes based on the device type:
<ul dir="auto">
<li><code>mobile</code>: Size for mobile devices (e.g., "80%").</li>
<li><code>tablet</code>: Size for tablets (e.g., "40%").</li>
<li><code>desktop</code>: Size for desktops (e.g., "40%").</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>

</ul>
<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h3 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Categories and Apis</h3><a id="user-content-categories-and-apis" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: Categories and Apis" href="https://github.com/alzzhosting/kenz-api/blob/main/README.md#categories-and-apis"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<p dir="auto">Organize APIs into categories for better navigation:</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Category Name (e.g., "AI (Artificial Intelligence)")</strong>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><code>items</code>: Define individual APIs within the category.
<ul dir="auto">
<li><code>name</code>: The name of the API (e.g., "LuminAI").</li>
<li><code>desc</code>: A short description of the API (e.g., "Talk with luminai").</li>
<li><code>path</code>: The endpoint path for the API (e.g., /ai/luminai?text=).</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>

<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h1 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Support</h1><a id="user-content-support" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: Support" href="https://github.com/alzzhosting/kenz-api/blob/main/README.md#support"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<p dir="auto">This project is designed to be easily deployable on various platforms. You can host it on any platform that supports Node.js applications. Some popular options include:</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong><a href="https://vercel.com/" rel="nofollow">Vercel</a></strong>: Easy deployment with minimal configuration.</li>
<li><strong><a href="https://www.heroku.com/" rel="nofollow">Heroku</a></strong>: A platform-as-a-service for deploying, managing, and scaling apps.</li>
<li><strong><a href="https://www.netlify.com/" rel="nofollow">Netlify</a></strong>: A platform for deploying static sites and serverless functions.</li>
<li><strong><a href="https://www.digitalocean.com/" rel="nofollow">DigitalOcean</a></strong>: Cloud infrastructure for deploying apps with more control over the environment.</li>
<li><strong><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/" rel="nofollow">AWS</a></strong>: Amazon Web Services for scalable and customizable cloud hosting.</li>
<li><strong><a href="https://railway.app/" rel="nofollow">Railway</a></strong>: A platform for deploying apps with easy integration and deployment steps.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">Make sure your platform supports Node.js, and configure it to run your API according to the platform’s deployment guidelines.</p>
<p dir="auto">If you need help with deployment, feel free to reach out to the creator or check the documentation of your chosen platform.</p>
